<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-11-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="886" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-11-25"><hi rend="italic">November 25,
                                    1896</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Telegram from Harpoot that twenty-six wives with children of naturalized
                            Americans, for whom I applied to the Sultan, will leave there at once
                            for America under escort of my cavas to the seashore, and that
                            twenty-three more such women and naturalized Americans not yet ready
                            will leave in a few days. Also a telegram from Marash that the governor
                            there facilitates departure of all persons applied for by me. Until now
                            the governor of Harpoot has obstructed the orders of the Porte.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>